http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/%E2%80%98Quality-of-work-has-improved%E2%80%99/article13998573.ece

Chairman of the Hyderabad Karnataka Region Development Board (HKRDB) and Municipal Administration Minister Qamarul Islam has said that there has been a qualitative and quantitative improvement in achieving progress in the works taken up by the HKRDB since October 2014.Briefing presspersons after the third board meeting here on Monday, Mr. Qamarul Islam said that from October 2014 to December 2015, the HKRDB spent Rs. 355 crore of the Rs. 820 crore released by the government, for an achievement of 43 per cent. This was in comparison to the expenditure of Rs. 110 crore in the five years from 2009 to 2013. He said that by March 2016, the board proposes to spend an additional Rs. 250 crore and complete all pending works of 2013-14 and also getting 75 per cent of the works taken up in 2014-15 ready. Mr. Qamarul Islam said that in 2016-17 the board would clear the backlog of 2015-16.